Notes:        
    
        -Saito paper conclusions
        1) 50 basis functions, r={0.003...40} is enough for Z=1-92
        2) phi(r)=sum{Bi}, and phi(r)=1/r * sum{Bi} both work
        3) Z=1-56 K=9 vs K=6: K=6 give faster and lower HF energies.
        4) Z=1-56 phi(r)=1/r option gives slighty better results for K=6.
        5) Z=92: 

